As regards earthly laws, those clergymen are to blame who meddle exclusively with human statutes, those of the Popes and Emperors, and neglect those of God.

Christ did not write his laws on rables, or on skins of dead animals, but in the hearts of men.²

ln other passages Wyclif is even more severe on the Pope, the Pope’s election and the power of the keys.
